Orang paling beruntung di dunia.

48
00:03:43,159 --> 00:03:46,829
<i>Ada titik pada 7.000 RPM</i>

49
00:03:47,038 --> 00:03:48,956
<i>ketika semuanya pudar.</i>

50
00:03:57,883 --> 00:04:00,677
<i>Mesin menjadi ringan.</i>

51
00:04:00,844 --> 00:04:01,928
<i>Lenyap begitu saja.</i>

52
00:04:03,597 --> 00:04:04,598
Hei!

53
00:04:05,348 --> 00:04:06,558
Hati-hati!

54
00:04:11,021 --> 00:04:13,982
<i>Yang tersisa hanya tubuh</i>

55
00:04:14,066 --> 00:04:16,360
<i>bergerak menembus ruang
dan waktu.</i>

56
00:04:21,948 --> 00:04:23,867
<i>7.000 RPM.</i>

57
00:04:25,369 --> 00:04:26,620
<i>Di situlah kau menemukannya.</i>

58
00:04:30,624 --> 00:04:32,209
<i>Memberimu pertanyaan.</i>

59
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:34,586
<i>Satu-satunya pertanyaan
yang penting.</i>

60
00:04:38,298 --> 00:04:39,758
<i>"Siapakah dirimu?"</i>

61
00:04:46,723 --> 00:04:50,019
Von Trips di Ferrari,
memasuki tikungan.

62
00:04:50,186 --> 00:04:51,729
- Remnya telat.
- Kutelepon tiga kali

63
00:04:51,896 --> 00:04:53,064
dan kau tidak menjawab.

64
00:04:53,231 --> 00:04:55,525
- Dia cetak rekor baru!
- Kujawab setiap kali bunyi.

65
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:57,026
- Tidak benar.
- Benar.

66
00:04:57,235 --> 00:04:58,236
Tidak benar.

67
00:04:58,569 --> 00:05:00,321
Sebulan lalu,
mobil ini menyenangkan.

68
00:05:01,447 --> 00:05:04,492
Kini tak mau menyala.
Kalau menyala.

69
00:05:04,659 --> 00:05:05,910
suaranya begini...

70
00:05:06,703 --> 00:05:10,039
Saat keluar dari halaman,
anjingnya kena serangan jantung.

71
00:05:11,165 --> 00:05:12,709
Aku hanya minta buat seperti dulu.

72
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:16,921
Katup dan businya kotor.

73
00:05:17,004 --> 00:05:19,173
Mobilnya tak bermasalah,
tapi pemakaiannya.

74
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,258
Pemakaiannya?

75
00:05:20,341 --> 00:05:22,677
Banyak bensin, kurang percikan.
Jadi meletup.

76
00:05:22,844 --> 00:05:24,178
Jelaskan dengan bahasa awam.

77
00:05:26,764 --> 00:05:27,890
Baik.

78
00:05:29,183 --> 00:05:30,184
Jadi...

79
00:05:31,185 --> 00:05:34,188
Itu adalah mobil sport.

80
00:05:34,397 --> 00:05:36,482
Kendarai seperti mobil sport.

81
00:05:36,607 --> 00:05:39,737
Kalau seperti guru sekolah,
mesinnya akan tersumbat.

82
00:05:39,903 --> 00:05:43,282
Coba ganti gigi pada 5.000 RPM,
bukan 2.000.

83
00:05:43,449 --> 00:05:47,870
Kendarai dengan cepat dan sigap.

84
00:05:47,953 --> 00:05:49,204
Mobilnya pasti aman.

85
00:05:49,329 --> 00:05:53,125
Maksudmu aku tak tahu cara
mengendarai mobilku?

86
00:05:54,001 --> 00:05:55,002
Tidak.

87
00:05:55,419 --> 00:05:56,962
Menurutku ini bukan mobilmu.

88
00:05:57,129 --> 00:06:00,799
Mobilmu lebih cocok
Plymouth atau Studebaker.

89
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,553
Kau punya masalah denganku?

90
00:06:05,679 --> 00:06:08,390
Aku tak punya masalah.
Aku punya MG. Berjalan mulus.

91
00:06:08,599 --> 00:06:10,017
Diam kau, Bodoh.

92
00:06:10,184 --> 00:06:11,393
Kembalikan uangku.

93
00:06:11,477 --> 00:06:14,063
Tenang. Aku mau saja kembalikan.

94
00:06:14,229 --> 00:06:16,148
Tapi kau belum bayar
servis bulan lalu.

95
00:06:16,231 --> 00:06:18,484
Di negara ini,
pelanggan selalu benar.

96
00:06:18,609 --> 00:06:19,943
Pernah dengar itu?

97
00:06:20,027 --> 00:06:21,820
Ya.

98
00:06:21,987 --> 00:06:23,739
Omong kosong.

99
00:06:23,906 --> 00:06:26,200
Ingat, kutingkatkan waktunya,

100
00:06:26,367 --> 00:06:29,286
jadi, sedikit waspada
di gigi satu.

101
00:06:29,411 --> 00:06:32,957
Tambah gasnya. Bagus.
Tambah gas.

102
00:06:37,962 --> 00:06:39,798
Pelanggan puas lainnya?

103
00:06:42,717 --> 00:06:44,219
Bisa kubantu, Nona?

104
00:06:46,262 --> 00:06:48,139
Bukankah itu MGA 1500?

105
00:06:50,392 --> 00:06:52,560
Kau tahu mobil.

106
00:06:52,727 --> 00:06:54,354
Aku suka mobil.

107
00:06:54,562 --> 00:06:56,189
Aku suka suaranya.

108
00:06:56,398 --> 00:06:58,108
Cara mobil melewatimu.

109
00:06:58,274 --> 00:06:59,192
Benar.

110
00:07:00,402 --> 00:07:01,903
Getarannya.

111
00:07:03,863 --> 00:07:09,703
Punyaku mobil Country Squire
berpanel kayu

112
00:07:09,786 --> 00:07:11,329
di seberang jalan.

113
00:07:12,580 --> 00:07:14,999
Mobil balap sejati.

114
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:16,084
Masa?

115
00:07:16,251 --> 00:07:17,919
- Cepatkah?
- Sangat.

116
00:07:18,586 --> 00:07:21,423
Tunggu. Kau gadis macam apa?

117
00:07:21,506 --> 00:07:24,135
Gadis yang menyukai aroma bensin.

118
00:07:24,218 --> 00:07:25,636
Karet yang terbakar.

119
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:28,931
Kau semacam gadis nakal?

120
00:07:29,014 --> 00:07:30,933
Sejak menikahimu.

121
00:07:38,983 --> 00:07:40,735
- Gar, ada apa?
- Ada sesuatu.

122
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:43,946
Hai, Lee.

123
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:46,073
Dia tidak seyakin dirimu
mengenai bank.

124
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:49,535
Aku meragukan ini

125
00:07:50,703 --> 00:07:52,163
Bagaimana ini bisa keluar?

126
00:07:55,374 --> 00:07:58,210
- Don, ada apa?
- Entah.

127
00:07:59,503 --> 00:08:00,629
Tn. Ford, selamat datang.

128
00:08:00,838 --> 00:08:02,673
- Selamat sore, Tn. Ford.
- Senang bertemu denganmu.

129
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:10,222
Tutup pabriknya, Tn. Beebe.

130
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:17,731
John!

131
00:08:22,402 --> 00:08:23,987
Semua berhenti.

132
00:08:34,956 --> 00:08:36,416
Dengar itu?

133
00:08:39,127 --> 00:08:43,131
Itu suara Ford Motor Company

134
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,801
bangkrut.

135
00:08:51,390 --> 00:08:56,937
Tahun 1899, kakekku, Henry Ford,

136
00:08:57,104 --> 00:09:00,399
berjalan pulang
dari Edison Illumination

137
00:09:00,482 --> 00:09:02,526
usai jam kerja ganda.

138
00:09:02,693 --> 00:09:04,695
Dia merenung.

139
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:10,076
Paginya, dia dapat ide
yang mengubah dunia.

140
00:09:10,284 --> 00:09:15,665
65 tahun
dan 47 juta mobil kemudian,

141
00:09:15,748 --> 00:09:18,000
apa warisannya?

142
00:09:19,836 --> 00:09:23,715
Dikalahkan oleh Chevy Impala.

143
00:09:28,136 --> 00:09:29,971
Ini yang aku ingin
kalian lakukan.

144
00:09:30,138 --> 00:09:31,889
Pulang jalan kaki.

145
00:09:35,184 --> 00:09:38,730
Sambil berjalan, merenunglah.

146
00:09:39,397 --> 00:09:45,111
Orang yang ke kantorku
membawa ide, boleh tetap bekerja.

147
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:49,365
Sementara
para pecundang lainnya,

148
00:09:49,741 --> 00:09:50,950
tetaplah di rumah.

149
00:09:51,117 --> 00:09:52,952
Kalian tidak cocok di Ford.

150
00:10:03,213 --> 00:10:04,465
Shelby!

151
00:10:07,551 --> 00:10:10,387
Aku melihatmu. Bangun, Kawan.

152
00:10:12,848 --> 00:10:14,475
- Hei!
- Pergilah.

153
00:10:14,558 --> 00:10:16,810
Ayo. Kau bisa.

154
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:19,271
Ayo, Sayang.

155
00:10:19,438 --> 00:10:21,648
Pukul 08.30, waktunya bekerja.

156
00:10:21,815 --> 00:10:22,900
Ayo.

157
00:10:23,692 --> 00:10:25,235
- Ayo.
- Pergilah.

158
00:10:25,444 --> 00:10:27,988
Ini pukul 08.30.
Waktunya bekerja.

159
00:10:29,239 --> 00:10:30,407
Ayo.

160
00:10:31,492 --> 00:10:32,493
Hei, Phil.

161
00:10:32,659 --> 00:10:33,786
Hei, Bob.

162
00:10:33,952 --> 00:10:35,245
Shelby ada?

163
00:10:35,412 --> 00:10:37,122
Mungkin.

164
00:10:42,795 --> 00:10:45,089
Shelby, kau bangun pagi.

165
00:10:45,255 --> 00:10:48,384
Burung yang keluar pagi hari
dapat cacing, Pak Tua.

166
00:10:52,764 --> 00:10:54,099
Kau mencemaskan siapa?

167
00:10:54,224 --> 00:10:57,227
Ada Red Faris dan Bill Rushton.

168
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:58,812
Mereka di 327.

169
00:10:58,895 --> 00:11:00,355
Corvette.
Bagaimana dengan Bondurant?

170
00:11:00,438 --> 00:11:02,190
Masih mengemudi untuk Washburn.

171
00:11:02,273 --> 00:11:04,275
Tn. Shelby,
boleh minta tanda tangan?

172
00:11:04,943 --> 00:11:06,736
Nomor 614.

173
00:11:07,612 --> 00:11:08,988
- Terima kasih.
- Ya, santai saja.

174
00:11:09,155 --> 00:11:11,074
Kita akan kalahkan Corvette itu.

175
00:11:11,282 --> 00:11:14,494
Kita lebih ringan dan cepat,
jika tak cukup, kita lebih gahar.

176
00:11:14,828 --> 00:11:16,955
<i>Ayah, sebelum balapan dimulai,</i>

177
00:11:17,163 --> 00:11:18,832
<i>bawa anakmu ke Sekolah
Pengemudi Willow Springs.</i>

178
00:11:18,998 --> 00:11:22,085
Phil, beri kami
kelonggaran hari ini.

179
00:11:26,297 --> 00:11:27,298
Kau tidak apa-apa?

180
00:11:27,424 --> 00:11:30,343
Paragraf 15.4, bab 2b
dari peraturan SCCA

181
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:32,846
mengharuskan
semua mobil kelas AF memiliki

182
00:11:33,012 --> 00:11:37,100
bagasi minimal seluas 50 cm
kali 30 cm kali 15 cm.

183
00:11:37,225 --> 00:11:38,685
Bagasimu tidak menutup.

184
00:11:38,852 --> 00:11:40,854
- Maka tak memenuhi standar.
- Apa?

185
00:11:40,979 --> 00:11:44,358
Maka mobil didiskualifikasi
dari kompetisi Kelas A.

186
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:46,235
Dengar. Boleh aku bertanya?

187
00:11:46,444 --> 00:11:49,071
Ketika masih kecil,
apa kau berpikir

188
00:11:49,155 --> 00:11:53,576
"Saat besar, aku mau pergi
ke Willow Springs Raceway

189
00:11:53,659 --> 00:11:55,953
dan menggunakan
paragraf 15.4, bab 2b

190
00:11:56,078 --> 00:11:58,914
peraturan SCCA
mengenai kapasitas bagasi"?

191
00:11:59,123 --> 00:12:00,624
- Cukup.
- Benarkah?

192
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:03,919
Kau dan tim didiskualifikasi
dari balapan ini.

193
00:12:05,713 --> 00:12:07,631
Ternyata Lance Reventlow.

194
00:12:08,049 --> 00:12:09,675
- Shelby.
- Apa kabar, Lance?

195
00:12:09,759 --> 00:12:10,801
- Pak Tua.
- Hei, Lance.

196
00:12:10,885 --> 00:12:12,303
Perkenalkan Dieter Voss.

197
00:12:12,386 --> 00:12:13,596
Pengelola Brumos Porsche
di Jacksonville.

198
00:12:13,804 --> 00:12:15,347
Aku tahu tentang Tn. Voss.

199
00:12:15,514 --> 00:12:17,558
Musim yang baik
dengan Abarth itu, Pak.

200
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:19,560
Kau juga melihat hasil Cobra.

201
00:12:19,769 --> 00:12:21,604
- Terima kasih.
- Orangmu, Miles, luar biasa.

202
00:12:21,771 --> 00:12:23,355
- Kau mengikuti Miles?
- Ya.

203
00:12:23,564 --> 00:12:27,651
Dia juara USAC tahun '61.
Dia menang Pikes Peak Hill Climb.

204
00:12:27,818 --> 00:12:30,529
Juara SCCA kelas C
tiga tahun berurutan

205
00:12:30,696 --> 00:12:32,740
dengan MG bobrok
yang dia rakit sendiri.

206
00:12:32,865 --> 00:12:34,659
Kami dengar dia sulit diatur.

207
00:12:34,826 --> 00:12:36,703
Ken? Tidak. Dia jinak.

208
00:12:36,828 --> 00:12:38,830
Lance, beri tahu dia.
Kau balapan melawan Ken.

209
00:12:38,997 --> 00:12:41,917
Aku lebih sering di belakangnya
ketimbang melawannya.

210
00:12:42,125 --> 00:12:46,713
Brumos mencari pengemudi
untuk mobil nomor 2 di Sebring.

211
00:12:46,797 --> 00:12:47,964
- Benarkah?
- Bagaimana mungkin?

212
00:12:48,048 --> 00:12:50,008
Orangmu, Miles,
bisa mencapai target?

213
00:12:50,175 --> 00:12:52,177
- Ken
- Benarkah? Hei!

214
00:12:52,260 --> 00:12:56,264
Jim! Dia menaruh tas besar
di bagasimu?

215
00:12:56,348 --> 00:12:57,516
- Apa?
- Pelanggaran aturan.

216
00:12:57,599 --> 00:12:59,559
Permisi sebentar, Tuan-tuan.

217
00:12:59,768 --> 00:13:02,354
Jujur,
Ken dilahirkan untuk Sebring.

218
00:13:03,438 --> 00:13:09,027
Di sini tidak ada aturan
tentang bagasiku dan kopermu.

219
00:13:09,111 --> 00:13:11,863
Itu SCCA edisi tahun '62.

220
00:13:13,281 --> 00:13:17,452
Kau boleh jejalkan stiker ini
ke bokongmu.

221
00:13:17,619 --> 00:13:19,538
Halo, Bill. Ada masalah apa?

222
00:13:19,705 --> 00:13:21,581
- Mobil ini melanggar aturan.
- Bill sok tahu.

223
00:13:21,748 --> 00:13:23,125
- Bagasinya tak sesuai.
- Dia tidak serius.

224
00:13:23,291 --> 00:13:24,793
- Aku serius.
- Dia tidak serius.

225
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,546
- Aku sungguh berpikir
- Dia bercanda, Bill.

226
00:13:26,671 --> 00:13:28,423
Bill sok tahu.

227
00:13:28,589 --> 00:13:30,383
- Aku hanya mengerjakan tugas.
- Tunggu. Bill.

228
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:32,385
Dalam pengalamanku, ada
Dengarkan.

229
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:34,470
Selalu ada jalan tengah.

230
00:13:34,595 --> 00:13:36,514
- Ken kelewatan.
- Aku hanya mengerjakan tugas.

231
00:13:36,681 --> 00:13:38,975
Aku paham. Kau tahu sikapnya
